Peter Dada, Bola Bamigbola, Akure The Independent National Electoral Commission on Thursday commenced distribution of sensitive materials for the Saturday governorship poll. INEC Federal Commissioner supervising Ondo, Ogun and Lagos States, Dr. Adekunle Ogunmola, who spoke with newsmen at the premises of Central Bank of Nigeria, in Alagbaka, Akure, where the distribution of the materials took place, said the commission would improve on imperfections noticed during Edo governorship election. Ogunmola explained that the movement of electoral materials was being monitored with tracking devices. He said “As you can see, we are following our various timelines. We have designated today for the distribution of sensitive materials which we are doing now. We have reached 14 local government areas and it remains only four which we hope to complete in the next one hour. “As our materials have been loaded, so is our security also security men are entering the vehicles to different local government areas, so in terms of security, we are totally prepared. “There are some tracking devices in every vehicle. Those that left earlier have arrived at their local governments and by the grace of God, others will also get to their assigned local government areas. “I want to assure voters that what happened in Edo will be child’s play when it is compared with Ondo state, because we have learnt from the imperfections associated with Edo state to improve on our processes.” Copyright PUNCH.
